IS NULL

IS NULL operator to test whether a value is NULL or not.

To check if a value is not NULL, you use IS NOT NULL operator




IS NULL operator to find customers who do not have a sales representative:


SELECT 
    customerName, 
    country, 
    salesrepemployeenumber
FROM
    customers
WHERE
    salesrepemployeenumber IS NULL
ORDER BY 
    customerName;





IS NOT NULL operator to get the customers who have a sales representative


SELECT 
    customerName, 
    country, 
    salesrepemployeenumber
FROM
    customers
WHERE
    salesrepemployeenumber IS NOT NULL
ORDER BY 
   customerName;